race_comments: Martin Truex Jr. won the Bojangles' Southern 500 at Darlington Raceway, his fifth career NASCAR Sprint Cup Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated: No. 23 (engine change), Nos. 27, 31 (unapproved adjustments).
Carl Edwards won the Food City 500 at Bristol Motor Speedway, his 26th NASCAR Sprint Cup Series victory. No cars dropped to the rear of the field at the start of the race.

race_name: Bass Pro Shops NRA Night Race
race_comments: Kevin Harvick won the Bass Pro Shops NRA Night Race at Bristol Motor Speedway, his 33rd career NASCAR Sprint Cup Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following car dropped to the rear of the field for the reason indicated: #46 (driver substitution).

Jimmie Johnson won the Goody's Fast Relief 500 at Martinsville Speedway, his 79th career NASCAR Sprint Cup Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated: No. 17 (backup car) and No. 21 (unapproved adjustments).

race_name: Quaker State 400 Presented by Advance Auto Parts

race_comments: Kyle Busch won the Crown Royal presents the Combat Wounded Coalition 400 at the Brickyard at Indianapolis Motor Speedway, his 38th career NASCAR Sprint Cup Series victory.
